commit 99c5a2edaa89c38e86d35d3f1a2e690bd1f56143
Author: findingfaey <yifeiyangyang@gmail.com>
Date:   Wed Mar 12 15:39:14 2025 +0800

    Add customerdelete command for deleting customers

    - Implement DeleteCustomerCommand with customerdelete as the command word
    - Create DeleteCustomerCommandParser to handle customer deletion
    - Add JsonAdaptedCustomer for JSON serialization support
    - Update relevant model, parser, and test files to support customer deletion

    Rationale:
    Introduces a new command to delete customers from the address book,
    following the existing command design patterns and providing a consistent
    user experience for managing different entity types.

    Changes:
    - Added new command implementation for customer deletion
    - Updated AddressBookParser to route the new command
    - Modified test cases to support the new functionality
    - Ensured JSON serialization and model management for customers

    Example usage:
    - : Deletes the first customer in the displayed list

    Fixes:
    - Enables CLI-based customer deletion
    - Maintains type safety and follows existing architectural patterns
